const pageContent = "<div style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;\" class=\"pages\"><div id=\"K1402631969\" page-url=\"by-region\" class=\"page\"><a id=\"by-region\"></a><div class=\"page-layout\"><div class=\"page-content\"><bodycopy style=\"--fit-height: 10px; --resize-parent-width: 100%;\"><div class=\"region-header\">\n  <div class=\"page-label\">Explore by region</div>\n  <h1 class=\"region-title\">The <em>Known World</em></h1>\n</div>\n\n\n\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-europe\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>Europe</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <div class=\"panel-grid\">\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Italy · Emilia-Romagna</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/4-days-in-bologna/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Bologna: The Fat City’s Table</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A deeper guide to eating in Emilia-Romagna — the old country of ragù, mortadella, Parmigiano-Reggiano, and the settled conviction that lunch deserves reverence.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>4 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>September 2025</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Portugal · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/coming-soon/\">At the Edge of the Known World</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">Lisbon ends where the Atlantic begins, and at Cabo da Roca the traveller stood at the westernmost point of Europe.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>10 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>March</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\"><a href=\"/coming-soon/\">Greece · Europ</a>e</div><h3 class=\"card-title\">Islands at the End of Summer</h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">The ferry left Piraeus before dawn and by the time the sun was up the mainland had disappeared entirely.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>11 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>September</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\"><a href=\"/coming-soon/\">Spain · Europe</a></div><h3 class=\"card-title\">In the Shadow of the Alhambra</h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">Granada is a city that keeps its greatest treasure hidden until the very last moment.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>7 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>May</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\"><a href=\"/10-days-in-sevilla/\">Spain · Andalucía</a></div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/10-days-in-sevilla/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Andalucía Without Rush</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">Ten days in southern Spain’s triumvirate of Moorish inheritance — using Seville as a fixed base, making the region reveal itself not by conquest, but by return.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>10 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>September 2025</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\"><a href=\"/1-day-in-santiago-de-compostela/\">Spain · Europe</a></div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/1-day-in-santiago-de-compostela/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Santiago de Compostela — The End of the Pilgrim Road</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A day trip to the old pilgrim city from Porto — granite streets, cathedral shadow, and the strange hush that gathers where long roads finally end.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>1 day</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\"><a href=\"/3-days-in-madrid-the-capital-at-full-volume/\">Spain · Europe</a></div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/3-days-in-madrid-the-capital-at-full-volume/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Madrid — The Capital at Full Volume</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">Two days in Spain’s capital at full voltage — plazas, galleries, late meals, and the civic theatre of a city that refuses to lower its voice.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>2 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\"><a href=\"/1-day-in-colonia-guell/\">Spain · Europe</a></div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/1-day-in-colonia-guell/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Colonia Güell — Gaudí's Forgotten Blueprint</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A short journey to Gaudí’s unfinished crypt at Colonia Güell — a quiet architectural rehearsal for the impossible argument later made in Barcelona.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>Guide</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\"><a href=\"/4-weeks-portugal-to-spain-by-rail-road/\">Portugal &amp; Spain · Europe</a></div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/4-weeks-portugal-to-spain-by-rail-road/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Portugal to Spain by Rail and Road — The Complete Circuit</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A full Portugal and Spain circuit by rail and road — Porto, Lisbon, Andalucía, Madrid, Barcelona, and the smaller detours that gave the route its texture.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>Full circuit</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Portugal · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/4-days-in-mondim-de-basto/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Mondim de Basto — The Detour Into the Mountains</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A mountain detour in northern Portugal — river valleys, granite villages, slow roads, and the kind of pause that changes the shape of a journey.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>Guide</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Portugal · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/5-days-in-porto-the-city-the-river-built/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Porto — The City the River Built</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">Four days in Porto, where the Douro cuts through stone and the city gathers itself in terraces, tiled churches, taverns, bridges, and river light.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>4 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Portugal · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/2-days-in-evora/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Évora — The Town of Bones and Roman Stone</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A guide to Évora’s Roman temple, whitewashed lanes, chapel of bones, and Alentejo stillness — a town where history feels close enough to touch.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>Guide</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Portugal · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/douro-valley-day-trip/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">The Douro Valley — A Day Among the Terraced Vines</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A day through the Douro Valley’s terraced vineyards, river bends, station tiles, and slow wine-country distances from Porto.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>1 day</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Spain · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/1-day-in-tarragona-sitges/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Tarragona and Sitges — Roman Stone and Seaside Light</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A Barcelona day trip split between Tarragona’s Roman remains and Sitges’ bright coastal ease — stone, sea air, and a softer edge of Catalonia.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>1 day</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Spain · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/1-day-in-figueres-girona/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Figueres and Girona — A Day Inside Dalí's Mind</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A Catalonia day trip through Dalí’s theatrical museum in Figueres and Girona’s medieval lanes, where surrealism gives way to stone and riverlight.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>1 day</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Spain · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/2-days-in-caceres/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Cáceres — A Medieval City Held in Amber</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A guide to Cáceres, the Extremaduran city of towers, plazas, and preserved medieval silence — a place that seems to resist the present tense.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>Guide</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Portugal · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/5-days-in-lisbon-itinerary/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Lisbon — Seven Hills and the Sound of Fado</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">Five days in Lisbon across miradouros, tiled streets, trams, fado rooms, river light, and the steep grammar of a city built on seven hills.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>5 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Portugal · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/1-day-in-sintra-the-mountain-of-romantic-follies/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Sintra — The Mountain of Romantic Follies</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A day trip to Sintra’s palaces, forests, steep roads, and Romantic excess — where the mountain turns architecture into theatre.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>1 day</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Spain · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/4-days-in-valencia-itinerary/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Valencia — Where the River Became a Garden</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A guide to Valencia’s old quarter, market halls, beaches, paella country, and the Turia — the riverbed remade as the city’s long green spine.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>Guide</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Portugal · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/4-days-in-lagos-the-coast-of-golden-cliffs/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Lagos — The Coast of Golden Cliffs</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A guide to Lagos and the Algarve coast — golden cliffs, sea caves, old walls, and the Atlantic light that sharpens every edge.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>Guide</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Spain · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/7-days-in-barcelona/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Barcelona — Gaudí's Unfinished Argument</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">Seven days in Barcelona through Gaudí’s monuments, Gothic streets, markets, seaside edges, and the unfinished argument rising above the city.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>7 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Summer 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Italy · Lazio</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/six-days-in-rome-at-the-table-of-empires/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Rome: Six Days at the Table of Empires</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">Six days in Rome at the table of empires — ruins, churches, piazzas, trattorias, and the old imperial appetite still moving beneath the stone.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>6 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>September 2025</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">San Marino · Europe</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/san-marino-day-trip-guide/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">San Marino: Upon the Rock of the Oldest Republic</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A day trip from Bologna to the old republic on the mountain — towers, steep streets, and the strange endurance of a country built into stone.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>1 day</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>September 2025</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Spain · Andalucía</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/1-day-in-cordoba/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">The City Between Empires — One Day in Córdoba</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A day trip from Seville to Córdoba — mosque-cathedral shadow, Roman stone, orange courtyards, and the city caught between its empires.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>1 day</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Autumn 2024</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Spain · Andalucía</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/1-day-in-cadiz/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Cádiz — At the Edge of the Known World</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A day trip to Cádiz, where the old city narrows toward the Atlantic — sea walls, bright plazas, fried fish, and the edge of Spain facing outward.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>1 day</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Autumn 2024</span></div></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-north-africa\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>North Africa</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <div class=\"panel-grid\">\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Morocco · North Africa</div><h3 class=\"card-title\">Into the Red City and Beyond</h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">The medina swallowed the traveller whole — a labyrinth of spice and shadow older than any map.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>9 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>April</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Morocco · Imperial Cities</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/the-imperial-circuit-morocco-in-14-days/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">The Imperial Circuit: Morocco in 14 Days</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">Marrakech to Rabat to Fes to Tangier — a standalone journey through Morocco’s old capitals, with the road running from red walls and desert light to medina shadow, Atlantic wind, and the northern strait.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>14 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>September 2025</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Morocco · Fez</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/2-days-in-fez-itinerary/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Fez: Into the Labyrinth of the Eternal City</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A guide to Fez and its ancient medina — blue gates, tannery light, narrow lanes, and the feeling of entering a city built before the map learned restraint.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>Guide</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Morocco</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Morocco · Tangier</div><h3 class=\"card-title\"><a href=\"/3-days-in-tangier-at-the-edge-of-two-worlds/\" style=\"color:inherit;text-decoration:none;\">Tangier: At the Edge of Two Worlds</a></h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">A guide to Tangier at the meeting of sea roads — medina hills, café terraces, Atlantic wind, and the narrow strait between continents.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>Guide</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>Morocco</span></div></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-west-africa\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>West Africa</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <p class=\"panel-empty\">The road has not yet reached these shores. But the traveller is patient.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-east-africa\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>East Africa</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <p class=\"panel-empty\">The road has not yet reached these shores. But the traveller is patient.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-middle-east\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>Middle East</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <div class=\"panel-grid\">\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Turkey · Middle East</div><h3 class=\"card-title\">Between Two Continents</h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">Istanbul does not belong to any single world — it stands at the crossing of many.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>8 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>October</span></div></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-south-asia\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>South Asia</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <p class=\"panel-empty\">The road has not yet reached these shores. But the traveller is patient.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-southeast-asia\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>Southeast Asia</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <div class=\"panel-grid\">\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Vietnam · Southeast Asia</div><h3 class=\"card-title\">The Long Road from Hanoi</h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">They boarded the night train south as the city was going to sleep, and woke to mountains entirely unknown.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>18 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>February</span></div></div>\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Thailand · Southeast Asia</div><h3 class=\"card-title\">North of Bangkok, Toward the Mountains</h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">Chiang Mai arrived slowly, the way all good cities do — first as a rumour, then as a smell of jasmine.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>12 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>January</span></div></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-east-asia\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>East Asia</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <div class=\"panel-grid\">\n    <div class=\"panel-card\"><div class=\"card-region\">Japan · East Asia</div><h3 class=\"card-title\">Where the Temples Keep Their Silence</h3><p class=\"card-excerpt\">Kyoto in November is a city made entirely of farewells — each maple leaf a small, burning letter of departure.</p><div class=\"card-meta\"><span>14 days</span><span class=\"dot-sep\"></span><span>November</span></div></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-central-asia\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>Central Asia</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <p class=\"panel-empty\">The road has not yet reached these shores. But the traveller is patient.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-north-america\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>North America</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <p class=\"panel-empty\">The road has not yet reached these shores. But the traveller is patient.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-central-america\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>Central America</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <p class=\"panel-empty\">The road has not yet reached these shores. But the traveller is patient.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-south-america\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>South America</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <p class=\"panel-empty\">The road has not yet reached these shores. But the traveller is patient.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"region-panel open\" id=\"panel-oceania\">\n  <div class=\"panel-header\">\n    <h2 class=\"panel-title\"><em>Oceania</em></h2>\n    \n  </div>\n  <p class=\"panel-empty\">The road has not yet reached these shores. But the traveller is patient.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n</bodycopy></div></div></div></div>";
